    \item[4] \emph{Conditions}: Set $L$ denotes the conditions.

\end{itemize}
\setlength{\leftskip}{0pt}

Now, let's represent the logical and mathematical representation of Goals and Conditions.

\begin{itemize}[label=\textbf{G}.\arabic*.]
    \item[1] \emph{Goal 1}: $z_1 = z_{11}$ (Logical: ID = 1, Name = Goal 1)
    \item[2] \emph{Goal 2}: $z_2 = z_{21}$ (Logical: ID = 2, Name = Goal 2)

\begin{itemize}[label=\textbf{C}.\arabic*.]
    \item[1] \emph{Condition 1}: $c_1$ (ID = 1, Name = Condition 1)
    \item[2] \emph{Condition 2}: $c_2$ (ID = 2, Name = Condition 2)
\end{itemize}

Finally, let's define the optimization model.

$$
\begin{aligned}
& \text{Minimize} & & z = \sum_{i \in I} x_i \\

& & & c_2 = \text{True} \\
